# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# uvicorn is the **ASGI web server** for Python — the
# de-facto standard ASGI server (alongside hypercorn /
# daphne).  Used to serve FastAPI / Starlette / Django
# (ASGI mode) / Litestar / etc.  Pivots from Go testing
# tooling (R265 moq) into the **Python web serving
# cluster**.  Sister to gunicorn (not yet in corpus) and
# hypercorn.
#
# Critical extraction note: uvicorn uses **Python Click**
# library at `import click` — corpus's **first
# documented Python Click CLI**.  Documents the
# **3-way Python CLI library taxonomy**: (a) **argparse**
# (Python stdlib; most primitive; required-arg-by-default
# semantics), (b) **Click** (most popular; decorator-
# based; auto-help; subcommand support; THIS CLI), (c)
# **Typer** (modern; type-hint-driven; built on Click
# but with cleaner ergonomics).  Plus minor libs: (d)
# docopt (parses help-text format), (e) fire (auto-CLI
# from any Python obj).  Documents the **Click decorator
# pattern**: `@click.command(...)` decorates the main
# fn; `@click.argument(name, ...)` for positionals;
# `@click.option(name, ...)` for flags; decorators STACK
# in REVERSE order (last decorator = first arg in fn
# signature).  Distinct from Rust clap derive's struct-
# based approach.  Click is the dominant Python CLI lib —
# used by Flask/Django-CLI/Black/many more.
#
# Critical extraction note: uvicorn uses
# **`@click.command(context_settings={"auto_envvar_prefix":
# "UVICORN"})`** at main.py:62 — the **AUTO-ENV-VAR-
# PREFIX feature** in Click.  Every option automatically
# gets a `UVICORN_<NAME>` env var fallback (with the
# option name uppercased + underscores instead of
# dashes).  E.g. `--host` reads from `UVICORN_HOST`,
# `--port` from `UVICORN_PORT`, `--workers` from
# `UVICORN_WORKERS`.  Documents the **auto-envvar-prefix
# pattern** — distinct from R252 saya's `#[clap(long,
# env)]` Rust shorthand (which auto-derives env names
# but requires the attribute on every flag).  Click's
# `auto_envvar_prefix` is GLOBAL — set once on the
# command, applies to every option.  Distinct from R260
# dua's SYSTEMATIC `DUA_*` env names declared on each
# flag — uvicorn's auto-prefix is implicit.  Corpus's
# **first documented auto-envvar-prefix** Click feature.
#
# Critical extraction note: uvicorn uses **`@click.argument
# ("app", envvar="UVICORN_APP")`** at main.py:63 — the
# POSITIONAL `app` (the ASGI application import path
# like `mymodule:app`) has an explicit env var override.
# Plus the positional is REQUIRED (Click's default for
# arguments).  Documents the **Click argument vs option
# distinction**: argument = positional + required by
# default; option = flag-prefixed + optional by default.
# Plus the env var on argument is OVERRIDDEN if the
# positional is provided on CLI.  Distinct from R252
# saya's `#[clap(long, env)]` (flag with env) — Click's
# `@click.argument(envvar=...)` is **positional with
# env-var fallback**.  Corpus's **first documented
# Click argument-envvar pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: uvicorn uses **`@click.option
# ("--reload-dir", "reload_dirs", multiple=True, ...)`**
# at main.py:82-87 — TWO key Click features:
#   1. **Renamed parameter** — the option is `--reload-
#      dir` (singular, kebab-case) on the CLI, but the
#      Python parameter that receives the value is
#      `reload_dirs` (plural, snake_case).  The second
#      positional string to `@click.option` is the
#      DESTINATION variable name.
#   2. **`multiple=True`** — the option can be specified
#      multiple times; the destination becomes a `tuple`
#      of values (or empty tuple if never specified).
#      E.g. `--reload-dir /a --reload-dir /b` →
#      `reload_dirs = ("/a", "/b")`.
# Documents the **renamed-destination + multiple flag
# pattern** — Click's standard idiom for "repeatable
# option that collects into a Python sequence".  Distinct
# from clap derive's `Vec<T>` field (which auto-derives
# both the multiple semantics and the collection type).
# Plus `type=click.Path(exists=True)` validates that the
# path exists at parse time.  Corpus's **first documented
# click.Path validator**.
#
# Critical extraction note: uvicorn uses **`--access-log/
# --no-access-log` PAIRED ENABLE/DISABLE FLAG** at
# main.py:213-218 — the option name uses the
# `--FLAG/--no-FLAG` slash-separated SYNTAX which Click
# recognizes specially.  This generates BOTH `--access-
# log` (sets to True) AND `--no-access-log` (sets to
# False).  Documents the **click slash-paired enable/
# disable syntax** — distinct from R248 cairo-coverage's
# clap pattern (`#[arg(action = ArgAction::SetTrue)]`
# for True-only + separate explicit `--no-X` flag).
# Click bundles both forms into one decorator.  uvicorn
# uses this for 5 flags: --access-log, --use-colors,
# --proxy-headers, --server-header, --date-header — all
# defaulting to True with the `--no-X` form for explicit
# disable.  Corpus's **first documented Click slash-
# paired enable/disable syntax**.
#
# Critical extraction note: uvicorn uses **`--version`
# with `callback=print_version, expose_value=False,
# is_eager=True`** at main.py:353-360 — the **EAGER
# CALLBACK pattern** in Click:
#   - `callback=print_version` — fn to invoke when the
#     flag is parsed
#   - `expose_value=False` — DO NOT pass `version` as a
#     parameter to the main fn (callback handles it)
#   - `is_eager=True` — process this option BEFORE other
#     options (so `--version` works even if other
#     required args missing)
# Documents the **Click eager callback** pattern —
# distinct from clap derive's `#[arg(action =
# ArgAction::Version)]` (which clap auto-handles).
# Useful for flags that short-circuit normal parsing
# (--help, --version, --completion, etc.).  Plus
# `callback` fn signature is `(ctx, param, value)` —
# 3-arg form.  Corpus's **first documented Click eager-
# callback pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: uvicorn uses
# **`type=click.Choice(list(LOG_LEVELS.keys()))`** at
# main.py:34 + 208 — the **Click Choice ValueParser**.
# Restricts the option to a fixed set of values.
# Distinct from clap's `value_parser = [...]` slice or
# ValueEnum-derive.  Documents the **Click Choice
# pattern** — accepts a list of strings; validates input
# at parse time; emits "invalid choice: 'X'. (choose
# from 'a', 'b', 'c')" on mismatch.  uvicorn uses 3
# Choice variants: LEVEL_CHOICES (6 levels: critical /
# error / warning / info / debug / trace), LIFESPAN_CHOICES
# (3 values: auto / on / off), INTERFACE_CHOICES (4
# values: auto / asgi3 / asgi2 / wsgi).
#
# Critical extraction note: uvicorn has **~50 options**
# decorated stacking on a single `main` fn — Click's
# decorator stacking is the standard idiom for non-
# subcommand CLIs.  The main fn signature reflects the
# stack ORDER REVERSED — last `@click.option` decorator
# = first parameter after the positional `app`.
# Documents Click's **decorator-stack semantics**:
# (1) decorators are applied bottom-up; (2) the OUTERMOST
# decorator (closest to `def main`) is parsed LAST; (3)
# argument order in the fn signature must match the
# decorator order (top-to-bottom).  Practical: keep the
# decorator stack in alphabetical or logical order to
# make the fn signature predictable.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line

# 6 LOG_LEVELS from config.py:34-41.
local -a log_levels=(critical error warning info debug trace)

# HTTP_PROTOCOLS from config.py:42-46.
local -a http_protocols=(auto h11 httptools)

# WS_PROTOCOLS from config.py:47-53.
local -a ws_protocols=(auto none websockets websockets-sansio wsproto)

# LIFESPAN from config.py:54-58.
local -a lifespans=(auto on off)

# LOOP_FACTORIES from config.py:59-64.
local -a loop_factories=(none auto asyncio uvloop)

# INTERFACES from config.py:65.
local -a interfaces=(auto asgi3 asgi2 wsgi)

_arguments -s -S \
  '(-h --help)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
  '--version[display the uvicorn version and exit (EAGER CALLBACK)]' \
  '--host=[bind socket to this host (default: 127.0.0.1; env: UVICORN_HOST)]:host:' \
  '--port=[bind socket to this port (0 = pick available; default: 8000; env: UVICORN_PORT)]:port:' \
  '--uds=[bind to UNIX domain socket (env: UVICORN_UDS)]:path:_files' \
  '--fd=[bind to socket from this file descriptor (env: UVICORN_FD)]:fd:' \
  '--reload[enable auto-reload (env: UVICORN_RELOAD)]' \
  '*--reload-dir=[reload directories (repeatable; multiple=True; click.Path exists=True)]:dir:_files -/' \
  '*--reload-include=[glob patterns to include while watching (default: *.py)]:pattern:' \
  '*--reload-exclude=[glob patterns to exclude while watching]:pattern:' \
  '--reload-delay=[delay between checks for reload (default: 0.25s)]:seconds:' \
  '--workers=[number of worker processes (env: UVICORN_WORKERS; default: $WEB_CONCURRENCY or 1; NOT valid with --reload)]:n:' \
  '--loop=[event loop factory (default: auto)]:factory:($loop_factories)' \
  '--http=[HTTP protocol implementation (default: auto)]:protocol:($http_protocols)' \
  '--ws=[WebSocket protocol implementation (default: auto)]:protocol:($ws_protocols)' \
  '--ws-max-size=[WebSocket max message size in bytes (default: 16777216)]:bytes:' \
  '--ws-max-queue=[WebSocket message queue max length (default: 32)]:n:' \
  '--ws-ping-interval=[WebSocket ping interval (seconds; default: 20.0)]:seconds:' \
  '--ws-ping-timeout=[WebSocket ping timeout (seconds; default: 20.0)]:seconds:' \
  '--ws-per-message-deflate=[WebSocket per-message-deflate compression (default: true)]:bool:(true false)' \
  '--lifespan=[lifespan implementation (default: auto)]:type:($lifespans)' \
  '--interface=[application interface (default: auto)]:interface:($interfaces)' \
  '--env-file=[environment configuration file]:file:_files -g "*.env"' \
  '--log-config=[logging configuration file (.ini / .json / .yaml)]:file:_files' \
  '--log-level=[log level (default: info)]:level:($log_levels)' \
  '(--no-access-log)--access-log[enable access log (default: enabled; PAIRED slash-syntax flag)]' \
  '(--access-log)--no-access-log[disable access log]' \
  '(--no-use-colors)--use-colors[enable colorized logging]' \
  '(--use-colors)--no-use-colors[disable colorized logging]' \
  '(--no-proxy-headers)--proxy-headers[enable X-Forwarded-Proto / X-Forwarded-For (default: enabled)]' \
  '(--proxy-headers)--no-proxy-headers[disable proxy headers]' \
  '(--no-server-header)--server-header[enable default Server header (default: enabled)]' \
  '(--server-header)--no-server-header[disable Server header]' \
  '(--no-date-header)--date-header[enable default Date header (default: enabled)]' \
  '(--date-header)--no-date-header[disable Date header]' \
  '--forwarded-allow-ips=[comma-separated trusted proxy IPs (env: FORWARDED_ALLOW_IPS; default: 127.0.0.1)]:ips:' \
  '--root-path=[ASGI root_path for submounted applications]:path:' \
  '--limit-concurrency=[max concurrent connections (issues HTTP 503 above limit)]:n:' \
  '--backlog=[max connections to hold in backlog (default: 2048)]:n:' \
  '--limit-max-requests=[max requests before terminating process]:n:' \
  '--limit-max-requests-jitter=[jitter to add to limit_max_requests (default: 0)]:n:' \
  '--timeout-keep-alive=[close Keep-Alive after N seconds without new data (default: 5)]:seconds:' \
  '--timeout-graceful-shutdown=[max seconds to wait for graceful shutdown]:seconds:' \
  '--timeout-worker-healthcheck=[max seconds to wait for worker healthcheck (default: 5)]:seconds:' \
  '--ssl-keyfile=[SSL key file]:file:_files -g "*.(pem|key)"' \
  '--ssl-certfile=[SSL certificate file]:file:_files -g "*.(pem|crt)"' \
  '--ssl-keyfile-password=[SSL keyfile password]:password:' \
  '--ssl-version=[SSL version (stdlib ssl module ints)]:n:' \
  '--ssl-cert-reqs=[client certificate requirement (stdlib ssl module ints)]:n:' \
  '--ssl-ca-certs=[CA certificates file]:file:_files -g "*.(pem|crt)"' \
  '--ssl-ciphers=[ciphers (stdlib ssl module string)]:ciphers:' \
  '*--header=[custom default HTTP response header (Name:Value; repeatable; renamed: headers)]:header:' \
  '--app-dir=[directory to look for APP in (added to PYTHONPATH; default: cwd)]:dir:_files -/' \
  '--h11-max-incomplete-event-size=[max bytes to buffer of an incomplete h11 event]:bytes:' \
  '--reset-contextvars[run each ASGI request in a fresh contextvars.Context]' \
  '--factory[treat APP as an application factory (() -> ASGI app callable)]' \
  '1:ASGI app import path (e.g. mymodule:app or factory:fn; env: UVICORN_APP):'
